title: PPPP’s Dost Muhammad wins PS- 52 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP), Dost Muhammad has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-52, Tharparkar-I , by securing 69,616 votes.
According to unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Sher Khan, Grand Democratic Alliance, who bagged votes 15,713.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 73.41 %.
